To determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$, we need to understand what $Y_7$ represents and how it relates to the given percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$. $Y_7$ is the seventh order statistic out of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution.

## Step 2
The probability that $Y_7 < 27.3$ can be approached by understanding that the event $Y_7 < 27.3$ is equivalent to having at least 7 observations out of 8 less than 27.3, since $Y_7$ is the seventh smallest value.

## Step 3
