## Step 4
To find $P\left(Y_7 < 27.3\right)$, we can use the binomial probability formula because we are dealing with a fixed number of independent trials (8 observations), each with a constant probability of success (being less than 27.3, which is 0.7).

## Step 5
$P\left(Y_7 < 27.3\right)$ is equivalent to the probability of having 7 or 8 observations less than 27.3. Using the binomial probability formula $P(X = k) = \binom{n}{k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k}$, where $n=8$, $p=0.7$, we need to calculate $P(X = 7) + P(X = 8)$.

