## Step 6
To find $P(X-Y>0)$, we need to standardize the value 0 to a z-score using the mean and standard deviation of $X-Y$. The z-score is given by $z = \frac{0 - (-1)}{5} = \frac{1}{5} = 0.2$.

## Step 7
