For $\bar{X} = 52.761$, $z = (52.761 - 54.030) / 0.846 = -1.269 / 0.846 = -1.5$.
For $\bar{X} = 54.453$, $z = (54.453 - 54.030) / 0.846 = 0.423 / 0.846 = 0.5$.

## Step 6
Using a standard normal distribution (Z-table), we look up the probabilities corresponding to the z-scores calculated. $P(Z \leq 0.5)$ and $P(Z \leq -1.5)$ are needed.

## Step 7
$P(Z \leq 0.5) \approx 0.6915$ and $P(Z \leq -1.5) \approx 0.0668$. Therefore, $P(-1.5 \leq Z \leq 0.5) = P(Z \leq 0.5) - P(Z \leq -1.5) = 0.6915 - 0.0668 = 0.6247$.

## Step 8
The probability that $\bar{X}$ falls within the given range is approximately 0.6247.

