Solution: ## Step 1
To find $P\left(A_1 \cup A_2 \cup A_3\right)$, we need to apply Theorem 1.1-6, which is the inclusion-exclusion principle for three events. The formula is given by $P\left(A_1 \cup A_2 \cup A_3\right) = P(A_1) + P(A_2) + P(A_3) - P(A_1 \cap A_2) - P(A_2 \cap A_3) - P(A_1 \cap A_3) + P(A_1 \cap A_2 \cap A_3)$.

